## 5. Primary Gameplay Loop

```text
1. SPAWN
   A mole appears with a word.

2. MIRROR
   Player states the ordinary or intuitive meaning.

3. HAMMER
   Player proposes meaningful fractures.

4. NAME
   Player names each fragment clearly.

5. DIFFERENTIATE
   Player explains why each fragment is distinct.

6. KINTSUGI
   Player maps relationships among fragments.

7. ZPC
   Player compresses the repaired word into a reusable object.

8. VALIDATE
   System checks coherence, coverage, novelty, and reconstructability.

9. SCORE
   Player receives dimension-level feedback.

10. ARCHIVE
   Strong entries enter the communal lexicon.

11. ADVANCE
   Conveyor moves and the next mole appears.
```

