## 7. Scoring Model

Each reconstruction receives a score from 0â100.

### Positive Dimensions

| Dimension | Weight | Question |
|---|---:|---|
| Intuitive Resonance | 10 | Does it begin from how people actually experience the word? |
| Distinctness | 15 | Are the fragments genuinely different? |
| Coverage | 15 | Do the fragments cover the important semantic territory? |
| Coherence | 15 | Does the repaired structure make sense as a whole? |
| Usefulness | 15 | Can the distinctions improve reasoning or action? |
| Compression Quality | 10 | Is the ZPC object compact without becoming lossy? |
| Reconstructability | 10 | Can another person expand the compressed form correctly? |
| Novelty | 5 | Does it reveal a non-obvious but defensible distinction? |
| Cross-Domain Transfer | 5 | Does it remain useful in another context? |

### Penalties

| Penalty | Typical Range |
|---|---:|
| Redundant fragments | -1 to -10 |
| Empty renaming | -1 to -10 |
| Unsupported jargon | -1 to -8 |
| Overfitting to one example | -1 to -8 |
| Category overlap left unexplained | -1 to -8 |
| Missing intuitive mirror | -1 to -10 |
| False precision | -1 to -10 |
| Excessive complexity | -1 to -10 |

### Score Bands

```text
90â100  Master Repair
80â89   Golden Seam
70â79   Strong Reconstruction
60â69   Useful Fracture
40â59   Partial Repair
20â39   Surface Crack
0â19    Missed Mole
```

